50|$|The Moroccan {{biometric}} passport {{was introduced in}} 2008. In December 2009, early limited trials have been extended, and the {{biometric passport}} is available from 25 September 2009 to all Moroccan citizens holders of an <b>electronic</b> <b>identity</b> <b>card.</b> It costs 300DH (approximately €27).|$|E
50|$|The Carta d'Identità Elettronica (<b>Electronic</b> <b>identity</b> <b>card,</b> CIE) is a {{personal}} identification document that replaced the paper-based identity card in Italy. The first Italian electronic identity cards were issued in 2001 and are now available to all Italian citizens 15 {{years of age and}} over.|$|E
