50|$|Italy {{introduced}} its <b>electronic</b> <b>identity</b> <b>cards,</b> called Carta d'Identità Elettronica (in Italy {{identified with the}} acronym CIE), to replace the paper-based ID card in Italy. Since 4 July 2016, Italy {{is in the process}} of renewing all ID cards to electronic ID cards.|$|R
